<item>
            <title>[KAFKA-1140] Move the decoding logic from ConsumerIterator.makeNext to next</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/KAFKA-1140</link>
                <project id="12311720" key="KAFKA">Kafka</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;Usually people will write code around consumer like&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;while(iter.hasNext()) {&lt;br/&gt;
try {&lt;br/&gt;
  msg = iter.next()&lt;br/&gt;
  // do something&lt;br/&gt;
}&lt;br/&gt;
catch{&lt;br/&gt;
}&lt;br/&gt;
}&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;hr /&gt;

&lt;p&gt;However, the iter.hasNext() call itself can throw exceptions due to decoding failures. It would be better to move the decoding to the next function call.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
